<title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title>

<statement>
  <p>¿Qué patrones observas en las tres columnas de la tabla de multiplicar?</p>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151461.svg">
    <shortdescription>Tabla de multiplicar con las columnas 2, 4 y 5 llenas.</shortdescription>
  </image>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample responses: To get \(4 \times 6\), for example, I can subtract 6 from \(5 \times 6\). This same pattern is true for the other numbers in the columns. Also, I can double \(2 \times 6\) to get \(4 \times 6\), and this pattern is also true for other numbers in the columns.</p>
</solution>

</exercise>
